						               													<description>A red storm is coming!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From beneath the ocean surface, boomer submarines from the six nuclear nations are preparing to launch their radioactive payload.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Con Sonar! your goal is to sink more enemy submarines than the other players, while making sure your own subs survive.  12 submarines are placed on the &amp;quot;firing solution&amp;quot; board at the beginning of the game.  Players play a fleet card to move a submarine up or down the board, by matching symbols on their other fleet cards or on the revealed torpedo cards, they can chain actions together and launch a torpedo.  If a torpedo is launching, dice are rolled and the higher a submarine is on the firing solution board, the more likely it is to be sunk.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Player score is based on the number of subs sunk, the number of surviving friendly subs, and various bonus objectives.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
